    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 2 SPEED REAR AXLES: SPICER - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>RING GEAR AND SUPPORT CASE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401507">Figure 7.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401507" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401507" filename="../figg14/G1401507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Ring Gear and Support Case - Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to disassembly, mark the right and left support case halves and ring gear for
                    reassembly in the same position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401508">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1401508" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401508" filename="../figg14/G1401508.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Ring Gear</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove ring gear bolts. Remove differential support case (L.H. half) using pry bars.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that whenever the ring gear bolts are removed, they be replaced.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove aluminum thrust washer plate.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Thrust washer plate may be retained in support case, due to oil retention. It should be
                            removed and cleaned before reassembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove planet gear mounting plate from assembly. Use care to avoid damage to surfaces of
                    plate and planet gear shafts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove planet gears and planet shafts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn assembly over and support on differential case dowel pins.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Care must be taken to keep differential subassembly properly positioned in support case to
                            prevent damage when removing ring gear.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate ring gear to make sure support case is seated squarely on differential
                    subassembly. Using a soft hammer, tap each side of ring gear alternately to remove from support case
                    half.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift support case from differential subassembly. Remove thrust washer from differential
                    subassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the right differential support case bearing is to be replaced, it may be removed as
                    shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401509">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1401509" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401509" filename="../figg14/G1401509.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Support Case Bearing Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the left differential support case bearing is to be replaced, it may be removed as
                    shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401509">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
